WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:00.797 --> 00:00:01.880
VINOD MARUR: Hi, everyone.

00:00:01.880 --> 00:00:03.400
How is everyone doing?

00:00:03.400 --> 00:00:04.859
Excited?

00:00:04.859 --> 00:00:06.900
So for those that don't
know me, I'm Vinod Marur.

00:00:06.900 --> 00:00:09.160
I'm a VP in the search
[INAUDIBLE] quality team

00:00:09.160 --> 00:00:11.140
here at Google.

00:00:11.140 --> 00:00:13.420
Over the years,
we've had the fortune

00:00:13.420 --> 00:00:17.440
of hosting some amazing
musicians and artists.

00:00:17.440 --> 00:00:21.480
I've been in your seats, eagerly
awaiting their appearance

00:00:21.480 --> 00:00:23.980
and wanting to ask
them questions.

00:00:23.980 --> 00:00:26.950
But it is an
exceptional honor to be

00:00:26.950 --> 00:00:29.150
able to host someone
of the caliber

00:00:29.150 --> 00:00:33.180
and the type of repertoire
that Ustad Zakir Hussain brings

00:00:33.180 --> 00:00:34.860
to us today.

00:00:34.860 --> 00:00:39.190
As many of you know, Ustadji
has won numerous awards--

00:00:39.190 --> 00:00:42.330
the Padma Shri, the Padma
Bhushan, the National

00:00:42.330 --> 00:00:47.240
Fellowship for Arts,
National Endowment, and also

00:00:47.240 --> 00:00:50.770
two Grammys, just to name a few.

00:00:50.770 --> 00:00:52.550
I did not realize
this until recently,

00:00:52.550 --> 00:00:57.650
but he began learning
tabla at the age of three.

00:00:57.650 --> 00:01:00.090
And he was touring
by the age of 11.

00:01:00.090 --> 00:01:04.140
His first tour to the
United States was in 1970.

00:01:04.140 --> 00:01:10.830
And his typical concert
here has 150 concert days.

00:01:10.830 --> 00:01:14.700
Just think about the
mind-boggling volume of that.

00:01:14.700 --> 00:01:16.290
And as I said, I've
been a huge fan.

00:01:16.290 --> 00:01:19.140
I remember seeing
Ustadji at places

00:01:19.140 --> 00:01:21.400
like [INAUDIBLE]
and Prithvi Theatre

00:01:21.400 --> 00:01:25.177
in Bombay, Madison Square
Garden in New York City,

00:01:25.177 --> 00:01:27.510
and, of course, closer to
home at the San Francisco Jazz

00:01:27.510 --> 00:01:28.530
Center.

00:01:28.530 --> 00:01:31.690
So it's really a personal
privilege for me,

00:01:31.690 --> 00:01:34.150
and please join me in a
huge round of applause

00:01:34.150 --> 00:01:35.945
in welcoming Ustadji to Google.

00:01:35.945 --> 00:01:40.912
[APPLAUSE]

